Egyptian Stocks: Delta Sugar, Orascom Construction Industries

-- B y   M a h m o u d   K a s s e m
-- 
2011-07-31T13:07:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-31/egyptian-stocks-delta-sugar-orascom-construction-industries.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30)  had
its first gain since July 17, increasing 0.3 percent to
5,035.63, as of the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo.  The following shares rose or fell. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Delta Sugar (SUGR EY) advanced for a second day, increasing
2.8 percent to 21.61 Egyptian pounds. Egypt’s Sugar & Integrated
Industries Co. plans to tender for 100,000 metric tons of raw
sugar in two phases starting this week, Al Mal newspaper
reported, citing the company’s Chairman Hassan Kamel.  Orascom Construction Industries (OCIC EY) rose the most
since July 20, adding 1 percent to 261.28 pounds. The
International Finance Corp. said it will buy shares in  Orascom
Construction Industries (OCIC) , Egypt’s biggest publicly traded
builder, and lend the company money.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mahmoud Kassem in Cairo at 
 mkassem1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  